    • testDerivedLocation

      public void testDerivedLocation()
      Test case for verifying the Location functionality.
      Parameters:
      X - The row in which the robot is located. In this test case, we set it 1.
      Y - The row in which the robot is located. In this test case, we set it 2.
      head - The situation of the robot's head. head is equal to EAST.
      mode - The situation of the robot's pen. mode is equal to UP.
      ArraySheet - The Floor that robot walk on it. ArraySheet is equal to (3, 3).

    • testUpdateLocationXOutOfRange

      public void testUpdateLocationXOutOfRange()
      Testing the UpdateLocation functionality when X is out of range.
      Parameters:
      Xpoint - Specifies the direction of the row for the movement of the robot. In this test case, we set it 1 and in the second step we set it -1.
      Ypoint - Specifies the direction of the column for the movement of the robot. In this test case, we set it 0.
      Step - The number of the steps that the robot should move. In this test case, we set it 1.

    • testUpdateLocationYOutOfRange

      public void testUpdateLocationYOutOfRange()
      Testing the UpdateLocation functionality when Y is out of range.
      Parameters:
      Xpoint - Specifies the direction of the row for the movement of the robot. In this test case, we set it 0.
      Ypoint - Specifies the direction of the column for the movement of the robot. In this test case, we set it 1 and then we set it -1.
      Step - The number of the steps that the robot should move. In this test case, we set it 1.

    • testUpdateLocationXYWithinRange

      public void testUpdateLocationXYWithinRange()
      Testing the UpdateLocation functionality when X and Y is in the range.
      Parameters:
      Xpoint - Specifies the direction of the row for the movement of the robot. In this test case, we set it 1.
      Ypoint - Specifies the direction of the column for the movement of the robot. In this test case, we set it 0.
      Step - The number of the steps that the robot should move. In this test case, we set it 1.
